page.title: 09RELIGION WARWICK BRIDGE
page.content: {St Leonerds} C of E was built by Thomas Parker in the 17th century. It has no clubs associated with it. {The CRUCIFIX }is near Aglionby.It is a land mark in a small garden beside a private wood.It is a wooden cross with a metal model of Jesus on it.It is a Roman Catholic monument. {OUR LADY AND St WILLFRED. This church is Roman Catholic. It was designed by Pugin the Younger. There are Methodist, Church of England,Roman Catholic churches in the area and a few people are Jehovahs Witnesses and go to church in Carlisle. We have not found any non Christian religious groups here.
